<subSubSection id="19996560FFA2C66BFF375431FB1DFCBE" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="description">
<paragraph id="513C36EBFFA2C66BFF375431FDBEFD5A" blockId="3.[136,1452,338,797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFF375431FE32FECE" bold="true" box="[136,423,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
In the protologue it is not mentioned the herbarium in which the type of 
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFB5D5430FAEDFECE" box="[1250,1400,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Pittier 12324</emphasis>
was allocated. According to the code (Art. 7.11, note 2, ex. 13), when the herbarium was not mentioned, all specimens of that gathering are 
<typeStatus id="8E388849FFA2C66BFEE654F8FE2EFE17" box="[345,443,411,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">syntypes</typeStatus>
and, therefore, a 
<typeStatus id="8E388849FFA2C66BFD3854F9FD7BFE16" box="[647,750,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">lectotype</typeStatus>
must be designated. Berg &amp; DeWolf (1975) were the first to name the material deposited in the NY herbarium as the 
<typeStatus id="8E388849FFA2C66BFCB954DDFCF8FE7A" box="[774,877,446,472]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">lectotype</typeStatus>
(in that work as “isotype”) and, therefore, must be followed (
<bibRefCitation id="35124B1AFFA2C66BFF435481FE4BFE5E" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[252,478,482,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" refId="ref7456" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="proceedings" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFEE05480FE0FFE5E" box="[351,410,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 7.11). Berg &amp; Villavicencio (2004) and Berg (2007) cite the VEN collection as a type (in these works as “ 
<typeStatus id="8E388849FFA2C66BFE075765FDB6FD83" box="[440,547,518,545]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">holotype</typeStatus>
”), but this must be corrected to the designation of Berg &amp; DeWolf (1975). The duplicate deposited at VEN has a label and a stamp called “ 
<typeStatus id="8E388849FFA2C66BFCA85749FC12FDE6" box="[791,903,554,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Holotype</typeStatus>
”, however, according to the code, the designation of a type is achieved only by effective publication (Art. 7.10). The code also warns that some of the material used by an author to describe a taxon may not be in the author’s herbarium (Art. 9A.1). Although 
<bibRefCitation id="35124B1AFFA2C66BFBF85711FB43FD2E" author="Pittier, H. F." box="[1095,1238,626,652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="44 - 80" refId="ref7155" refString="Pittier, H. F. (1937) Ensayo sobre la classificacion de las especies venezolanas del genero Ficus. Boletin de la sociedad venezolana de ciencias naturales 4: 44 - 80." type="journal article" year="1937">Pittier (1937</bibRefCitation>
, Introduction) says that many materials have been accumulated in the VEN herbarium, it is not possible to be sure that the type belongs to the herbarium. There are cases in Pittier’s work that the types were not found at VEN (ex.: 
<taxonomicName id="96834D68FFA2C66BFB1E57D8FE9BFD5B" authority="Pittier [1943: 257]" authorityName="Pittier" authorityPageNumber="257" authorityYear="1943" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corpulenta">
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFB1E57D8FAF5FD76" box="[1185,1376,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Ficus corpulenta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="35124B1AFFA2C66BFAD857D9FE9BFD5B" author="Pittier, H. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="257 - 260" refId="ref7190" refString="Pittier, H. F. (1943) Notas dendrologicas de Venezuela, Moraceae. Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Ciencias Naturales 8: 257 - 260." type="journal article" year="1943">Pittier [1943: 257]</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="35124B1AFFA2C66BFEA657BDFD8AFD5A" author="Pederneiras, L. C. &amp; Romaniuc-Neto, S. &amp; Mansano, V. D. F." box="[281,543,734,760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="244 - 250" refId="ref6730" refString="Pederneiras, L. C., Romaniuc-Neto, S. &amp; Mansano, V. D. F. (2018) Nomenclatural revision of Ficus sect. Americanae (Moraceae): typification of Ficus americana and allied species. Phytotaxa 361: 244 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 361.2.9" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pederneiras 
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFE1C57BCFE4EFD5A" box="[419,475,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="513C36EBFFA2C66BFF025661FB1DFCBE" blockId="3.[136,1452,338,797]" box="[189,1160,770,797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFF025661FE23FCBE" bold="true" box="[189,438,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Taxonomical note:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="96834D68FFA2C66BFE095660FDFEFCBE" authorityName="Pittier" authorityYear="1937" box="[438,619,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palmicida">
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFE095660FDFEFCBE" box="[438,619,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Ficus palmicida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized by Berg (2007) as 
<emphasis id="63F7EAF9FFA2C66BFBAE5660FB1DFCBE" box="[1041,1160,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName id="96834D68FFA2C66BFBAE5660FB11FCBE" box="[1041,1156,771,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pertusa">F. pertusa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
